citeinfo.title: Data for town of Wakefield, MA, complying with Level 3 of MassGIS digital parcel standard

dataqual.logic: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.

procstep.procdesc: Existing GIS parcel data was converted to MassGIS Level 3 template geodatabase and additional data layers and tables were added.
Spatial accuracy of data was verified using the parcel standard guidelines; town boundary was verified to be coincident with MassGIS Town Boundary layer. Polygon topology was updated and validated.

Multi-part polygons were created where necessary; internal polygon boundaries were dissolved where necessary; polygons representing legal boundaries such as easements or private right-of-ways were created. LOC_ID was updated

Updates were made to the data to reflect the most current version of the town's tax maps as of spring 2011, for the town's FY 2012. CAMA data was matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town Assessor. Final QAQC tools were run.

overview.dsoverv: Parcel data for the city of Wakefield, MA. FY 2013 annual parcel updates were done in April, 2012. Data was then upgraded to MassGIS Level III standards. Data represents boundaries of approximately 8625 properties, and corresponding information from the town's records of property assessment, including property address, use code and value. Data was updated through MassGIS Enhancement program in Spring 2018. Property boundaries are current as of April 2018; property record information is current as of January, 2018, and represent data for the the town's fiscal year 2018.

distinfo.resdesc: M305TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of Wakefield, MA that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M305Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M305OthLeg and M305Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http://www.mass.gov/mgis/stratplan.html), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.
